                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d33">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">758.6114AI/84: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Davis</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-07-21T19:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 21, 1920—7 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>765. Your telegram No. 1062 of July 14, 3 p.m. The President defers to your
                    desire not to serve on the League of Nations Commission which is to report to
                    the Council on the Aland Islands question. He would like to have Mr. Henry White
                    serve on the Commission as one of its members. You are instructed, therefore, to
                    convey to the Council an intimation of the President’s choice.</p>
                <p>Mr. White is believed to be at present in Europe. It is suggested that you get in
                    touch with him on this matter. It is thought that he is either in England or at
                    Scheveningen, the Netherlands.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Colby</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
